result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittany M Sands was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fraud on Taxicab Operator (<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.21(1m)(c).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
To be determined within 30 days.

  Restitution will be paid under the terms of a payment plan to be established with the agent but calling for no less than 2.5% of gross wages to be paid toward restitution and to be enforced through a wage assignment.
.

Def is not to consume or possess any alcohol or controlled substances without a prescription from licensed physician, with random screenings.
.

Upon successful completion of all terms and conditions of probation, the record will be expunged under 973.015.
.

Pay Crime Lab and Drug Assessment fee (see 'other' above for amount)

  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendent in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

  Pay DOC Supervision fees.

  Undergo any other assessments or evaluations deemed appropriate by PO and follow through with any treatment recommendations.

Credit for 15 days if probation revoked.
.

supervisions.notes:
Jail will be served in custody pending notification by Justice Support Services that the defendant has an acceptable residence.  JSS is to get the phone number of the def's mother and see if she will accept the def at her house while on Electronic Monitoring.  If def's mother agrees to this, the def will be released to her mother on Electronic Monitoring.  If def's mother does not agree to this, she will remain in jail until she can find another placement.  The Court finds that the Salvation Army is NOT an appropriate placement for the defendant
.
Concurrent with: Concurrent with La Crosse Co case 15CM43 and also 14CM1582 & 14CM1576
.
